OL,3,CPublic spending 'trade-offs' needed to
OL,4,Cmeet defence pledge, Cameron accepts
OL,6,FAsked whether public spending trade-
OL,7,Foffs beyond the civil service were
OL,8,Fneeded to fund the pledge, he said:
OL,9,F"All spending decisions are trade-offs
OL,10,Fbecause if you spend a pound on one
OL,11,Fthing you can't spend it on something
OL,12,Felse, and this is a very clear
OL,13,Fdemonstration of the Conservative
OL,14,FGovernment's priorities in terms of
OL,15,Fmaking this happen."
