OL,3,CPublic spending 'trade-offs' needed to
OL,4,Cmeet defence pledge, Cameron accepts
OL,6,FLord Cameron, who cut defence spending
OL,7,Fto 2.03% of GDP while he was in Number
OL,8,F10, added: "I've sat in the chair
OL,9,Fwhere you have to make decisions about
OL,10,Fwho gets what spending. This is a
OL,11,Freally important commitment because of
OL,12,Fthe challenges we face
OL,13,Finternationally."
OL,15,FMeanwhile, at a press conference in
OL,16,FBerlin, Mr Sunak was asked whether his
OL,17,Fdefence increase will mean tax rises
OL,18,Fand deep cuts, which he rejected as
OL,19,F"not a fair characterisation".
